32template <typename ResourceType, typename IDType>
33IDType AllocateEmptyObject(HandleAllocator *handleAllocator,
34 ResourceMap<ResourceType, IDType> *objectMap)
35{
36 IDType handle = FromGL<IDType>(handleAllocator->allocate());
37 objectMap->assign(handle, nullptr);
38 return handle;
39}
40
41} // anonymous namespace
42
43ResourceManagerBase::ResourceManagerBase() : mRefCount(1) {}
44
45ResourceManagerBase::~ResourceManagerBase() = default;
46
47void ResourceManagerBase::addRef()
48{
49 mRefCount++;
50}
51
52void ResourceManagerBase::release(const Context *context)
53{
54 if (--mRefCount == 0)
55 {
56 reset(context);
57 delete this;
58 }
59}
60
61template <typename ResourceType, typename ImplT, typename IDType>
62TypedResourceManager<ResourceType, ImplT, IDType>::~TypedResourceManager()
63{
64 ASSERT(mObjectMap.empty());
65}
66
67template <typename ResourceType, typename ImplT, typename IDType>
68void TypedResourceManager<ResourceType, ImplT, IDType>::reset(const Context *context)
69{
70 this->mHandleAllocator.reset();
71 for (const auto &resource : mObjectMap)
72 {
73 if (resource.second)
74 {
75 ImplT::DeleteObject(context, resource.second);
76 }
77 }
78 mObjectMap.clear();
79}
80
81template <typename ResourceType, typename ImplT, typename IDType>
82void TypedResourceManager<ResourceType, ImplT, IDType>::deleteObject(const Context *context,
83 IDType handle)
84{
85 ResourceType *resource = nullptr;
86 if (!mObjectMap.erase(handle, &resource))
87 {
88 return;
89 }
90
91 // Requires an explicit this-> because of C++ template rules.
92 this->mHandleAllocator.release(GetIDValue(handle));
93
94 if (resource)
95 {
96 ImplT::DeleteObject(context, resource);
97 }
98}

101ANGLE_DISABLE_WEAK_TEMPLATE_VTABLES_WARNING

106template class TypedResourceManager<Sync, SyncManager, GLuint>;
107template class TypedResourceManager<Framebuffer, FramebufferManager, FramebufferID>;
108template class TypedResourceManager<ProgramPipeline, ProgramPipelineManager, ProgramPipelineID>;
109ANGLE_REENABLE_WEAK_TEMPLATE_VTABLES_WARNING

138// ShaderProgramManager Implementation.
139
140ShaderProgramManager::ShaderProgramManager() {}
141
142ShaderProgramManager::~ShaderProgramManager()
143{
144 ASSERT(mPrograms.empty());
145 ASSERT(mShaders.empty());
146}
147
148void ShaderProgramManager::reset(const Context *context)
149{
150 while (!mPrograms.empty())
151 {
152 deleteProgram(context, {mPrograms.begin()->first});
153 }
154 mPrograms.clear();
155 while (!mShaders.empty())
156 {
157 deleteShader(context, {mShaders.begin()->first});
158 }
159 mShaders.clear();
160}
161
162ShaderProgramID ShaderProgramManager::createShader(rx::GLImplFactory *factory,
163 const gl::Limitations &rendererLimitations,
164 ShaderType type)
165{
166 ASSERT(type != ShaderType::InvalidEnum);
167 ShaderProgramID handle = ShaderProgramID{mHandleAllocator.allocate()};
168 mShaders.assign(handle, new Shader(this, factory, rendererLimitations, type, handle));
169 return handle;
170}
171
172void ShaderProgramManager::deleteShader(const Context *context, ShaderProgramID shader)
173{
174 deleteObject(context, &mShaders, shader);
175}
176
177Shader *ShaderProgramManager::getShader(ShaderProgramID handle) const
178{
179 return mShaders.query(handle);
180}
181
182ShaderProgramID ShaderProgramManager::createProgram(rx::GLImplFactory *factory)
183{
184 ShaderProgramID handle = ShaderProgramID{mHandleAllocator.allocate()};
185 mPrograms.assign(handle, new Program(factory, this, handle));
186 return handle;
187}
188
189void ShaderProgramManager::deleteProgram(const gl::Context *context, ShaderProgramID program)
190{
191 deleteObject(context, &mPrograms, program);
192}
193
194template <typename ObjectType, typename IDType>
195void ShaderProgramManager::deleteObject(const Context *context,
196 ResourceMap<ObjectType, IDType> *objectMap,
197 IDType id)
198{
199 ObjectType *object = objectMap->query(id);
200 if (!object)
201 {
202 return;
203 }
204
205 if (object->getRefCount() == 0)
206 {
207 mHandleAllocator.release(id.value);
208 object->onDestroy(context);
209 objectMap->erase(id, &object);
210 }
211 else
212 {
213 object->flagForDeletion();
214 }
215}

236
237TextureID TextureManager::createTexture()
238{
239 return AllocateEmptyObject(&mHandleAllocator, &mObjectMap);
240}
241
242void TextureManager::signalAllTexturesDirty() const
243{
244 for (const auto &texture : mObjectMap)
245 {
246 if (texture.second)
247 {
248 // We don't know if the Texture needs init, but that's ok, since it will only force
249 // a re-check, and will not initialize the pixels if it's not needed.
250 texture.second->signalDirtyStorage(InitState::MayNeedInit);
251 }
252 }
253}
254
255void TextureManager::enableHandleAllocatorLogging()
256{
257 mHandleAllocator.enableLogging(true);
258}

346// FramebufferManager Implementation.
347
348FramebufferManager::~FramebufferManager() = default;
349
350// static
351Framebuffer *FramebufferManager::AllocateNewObject(rx::GLImplFactory *factory,
352 FramebufferID handle,
353 const Caps &caps,
354 egl::ShareGroup *shareGroup)
355{
356 // Make sure the caller isn't using a reserved handle.
357 ASSERT(handle != Framebuffer::kDefaultDrawFramebufferHandle);
358 return new Framebuffer(caps, factory, handle, shareGroup);
359}
360
361// static
362void FramebufferManager::DeleteObject(const Context *context, Framebuffer *framebuffer)
363{
364 framebuffer->onDestroy(context);
365 delete framebuffer;
366}
367
368FramebufferID FramebufferManager::createFramebuffer()
369{
370 return AllocateEmptyObject(&mHandleAllocator, &mObjectMap);
371}
372
373Framebuffer *FramebufferManager::getFramebuffer(FramebufferID handle) const
374{
375 return mObjectMap.query(handle);
376}
377
378void FramebufferManager::setDefaultFramebuffer(Framebuffer *framebuffer)
379{
380 ASSERT(framebuffer == nullptr || framebuffer->isDefault());
381 mObjectMap.assign(Framebuffer::kDefaultDrawFramebufferHandle, framebuffer);
382}
383
384void FramebufferManager::invalidateFramebufferCompletenessCache() const
385{
386 for (const auto &framebuffer : mObjectMap)
387 {
388 if (framebuffer.second)
389 {
390 framebuffer.second->invalidateCompletenessCache();
391 }
392 }
393}

424// MemoryObjectManager Implementation.
425
426MemoryObjectManager::MemoryObjectManager() {}
427
428MemoryObjectManager::~MemoryObjectManager()
429{
430 ASSERT(mMemoryObjects.empty());
431}
432
433void MemoryObjectManager::reset(const Context *context)
434{
435 while (!mMemoryObjects.empty())
436 {
437 deleteMemoryObject(context, {mMemoryObjects.begin()->first});
438 }
439 mMemoryObjects.clear();
440}
441
442MemoryObjectID MemoryObjectManager::createMemoryObject(rx::GLImplFactory *factory)
443{
444 MemoryObjectID handle = MemoryObjectID{mHandleAllocator.allocate()};
445 MemoryObject *memoryObject = new MemoryObject(factory, handle);
446 memoryObject->addRef();
447 mMemoryObjects.assign(handle, memoryObject);
448 return handle;
449}
450
451void MemoryObjectManager::deleteMemoryObject(const Context *context, MemoryObjectID handle)
452{
453 MemoryObject *memoryObject = nullptr;
454 if (!mMemoryObjects.erase(handle, &memoryObject))
455 {
456 return;
457 }
458
459 // Requires an explicit this-> because of C++ template rules.
460 this->mHandleAllocator.release(handle.value);
461
462 if (memoryObject)
463 {
464 memoryObject->release(context);
465 }
466}
467
468MemoryObject *MemoryObjectManager::getMemoryObject(MemoryObjectID handle) const
469{
470 return mMemoryObjects.query(handle);
471}

482void SemaphoreManager::reset(const Context *context)
483{
484 while (!mSemaphores.empty())
485 {
486 deleteSemaphore(context, {mSemaphores.begin()->first});
487 }
488 mSemaphores.clear();
489}
490
491SemaphoreID SemaphoreManager::createSemaphore(rx::GLImplFactory *factory)
492{
493 SemaphoreID handle = SemaphoreID{mHandleAllocator.allocate()};
494 Semaphore *semaphore = new Semaphore(factory, handle);
495 semaphore->addRef();
496 mSemaphores.assign(handle, semaphore);
497 return handle;
498}
499
500void SemaphoreManager::deleteSemaphore(const Context *context, SemaphoreID handle)
501{
502 Semaphore *semaphore = nullptr;
503 if (!mSemaphores.erase(handle, &semaphore))
504 {
505 return;
506 }
507
508 // Requires an explicit this-> because of C++ template rules.
509 this->mHandleAllocator.release(handle.value);
510
511 if (semaphore)
512 {
513 semaphore->release(context);
514 }
515}
516
517Semaphore *SemaphoreManager::getSemaphore(SemaphoreID handle) const

519 return mSemaphores.query(handle);
